* Iron Raptor looked on in wonder as they entered into the huge ship, looking at every detail until Prowl pulled her closer to him, her attention then moving onto him.
Putting her hand on the one he had around her waist she smiled, always liking the feel of his strong arms around her.
Even wondering how she had lived before without knowing just what love was.
She listened to his soft voice, simply letting him take her body in any direction he wished. Not caring where as long as it was with him.
And as much as she just wanted to spend time with him now, she knew that if she didn�t repair then she wouldn�t be of any use to him at all.
Her wounds were fairly deep and there was no point in hiding that fact.
Her mech-fluid covered side making it very obvious.
Iron Raptor sighed and leaned her head against prowl�s shoulder again, closing her optics for a moment and resting them. Smiling at the thought of when she slept, Prowls arms holding her tightly.
There was no other thought in the universe as comforting as that. *
